From: Chuck Lever <chuck.lever@oracle.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Mar 2022 10:16:42 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] NFSD: Avoid calling fh_drop_write() twice in do_nfsd_create()
Git-commit: 14ee45b70dd0d9ae76fb066cd8c0652d657353f6
Patch-mainline: v5.19
References: git-fixes

Clean up: The "out" label already invokes fh_drop_write().

Note that fh_drop_write() is already careful not to invoke
mnt_drop_write() if either it has already been done or there is
nothing to drop. Therefore no change in behavior is expected.

Signed-off-by: Chuck Lever <chuck.lever@oracle.com>
Acked-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.com>

---
 fs/nfsd/vfs.c |    5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/fs/nfsd/vfs.c
+++ b/fs/nfsd/vfs.c
@@ -1523,7 +1523,6 @@ do_nfsd_create(struct svc_rqst *rqstp, s
 		case NFS3_CREATE_GUARDED:
 			err = nfserr_exist;
 		}
-		fh_drop_write(fhp);
 		goto out;
 	}
 
@@ -1531,10 +1530,8 @@ do_nfsd_create(struct svc_rqst *rqstp, s
 		iap->ia_mode &= ~current_umask();
 
 	host_err = vfs_create(&init_user_ns, dirp, dchild, iap->ia_mode, true);
-	if (host_err < 0) {
-		fh_drop_write(fhp);
+	if (host_err < 0)
 		goto out_nfserr;
-	}
 	if (created)
 		*created = true;
 
